Corporate Counsel: Operations
銳聯財智_香港商銳聯有限公司在臺辦事處
07/08 臺北市大安區

      5年以上工作經歷，大學以上學歷，待遇面議      
Rayliant’s “Corporate Counsel – Operations” is the firm’s in-house attorney responsible for providing legal advice relating to and oversight of the firm’s internal operations, including human resources, accounting, technology, and marketing. In representing and advising these departments, the firm’s Corporate Counsel will: 
 
develop and implement processes to provide suitable operational oversight and controls;  
review and negotiate vendor and internal legal agreements (e.g., service contracts, employment agreements, etc.);  
monitor and enforce compliance re all of the firm’s non-investment operations;  
take full responsibility for corporate governance obligations and timely filing of corporate governance documents with regulatory bodies;  
liaise with outside counsel, tax, and compliance vendors on a range of issues, including patents, trademarks, employment practices, and financial transactions;  
conduct legal research; and  
provide other legal support as required by firm’s legal and operations departments.  
 
The firm’s Corporate Counsel is a mid-level, full-time salaried position, reporting jointly to Rayliant’s General Counsel and the COO.







